9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 51, L.D. 87, “An Act Regarding the
10 State Workforce Board”
11 Amend the bill in section 6 in subsection 2-A in paragraph B in the last 3 lines (page
12 3, lines 3 to 5 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "The appointments of these members
13 are not subject to review by the joint standing committee of the Legislature having
14 jurisdiction over labor matters or confirmation by the Legislature." and inserting the
15 following: 'The appointments of these members are not subject to review by the joint
16 standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over labor matters or
17 confirmation by the Legislature.'
18 Amend the bill by inserting after section 6 the following:
19 'Sec. 7. 26 MRSA §2006, sub-§4, as amended by PL 2017, c. 110, §16, is further
20 amended to read:
21 4. Chair and vice-chair. The Governor shall appoint a chair from the members of the
22 board who represent business and industry and a vice-chair from the membership of the
23 board to serve for a one-year term. The appointment of the chair is subject to review by
24 the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over labor matters and
25 confirmation by the Legislature. The Governor may reappoint members to serve as chair
26 or vice-chair.
27 The Governor may appoint an interim chair for a one-time term of no more than 6 months.
28 The appointment of an interim chair is not subject to review by the joint standing committee
29 of the Legislature having jurisdiction over labor matters or confirmation by the Legislature.'
30 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
31 number to read consecutively.
32 SUMMARY
3333 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, amends the bill to
3344 require the appointment by the Governor of the chair of the State Workforce Development
